With great sadness and heartache our small but mighty Coop has left this earthly presence to join his bro Jackson 🪽🌈

Cooper was rescued in February 2011. 
He was about a year and a half old and had been picked up as a stray. We were looking for a playmate for puppy Jackson.  In a pen with 4-5 chihuahuas, we were blessed to find this adorable little beagle. 
That was the beginning of the much loved beaglebros ❤️

Cooper was an independent, strong willed, natural born leader.  He will always be remembered for having his own style of tough guy. Coop had a cocky strut we often described as “Tony Manero” from Saturday Night Fever. That, and the Jersey accent he had developed. He was flat out “cool dude” of the neighborhood. 

Over the past few months he had developed kidney disease and finally would not eat. His little body was becoming weaker each day. Friday morning he let us know it was time. He passed peacefully in momma’s arms at home surrounded by his loving family. 

Cooper 2009 - 12/15/2023
A life well lived. Always and Forever ❤️
